---


Author Name: **Jonathon Donaldson**
Original Redmine Issue: 806 from https://www.veripool.org
Original Date: 2014-07-28


---

I've been using verilator on my ubuntu linux box for a while now with great success. Now I want to be able to use verilator on my windows machine as well. I cloned the latest git repos and built the verilator binary successfully using cygwin's gcc, ran 'make test' which passed, and compiled my systemverilog design using verilator and the resulting binary worked as expected. So no major issues - which is awesome.

However, there is one thing that is bothering me...One thing that is different when compiling my SV design on linux vs windows is that I get a large number of the following warning messages about dllimport:

```
